Applying $N = \frac{F}{3}$, the equation becomes
$\frac{dF}{dt} = I - \frac{\alpha}{3}F^2$

For $t\rightarrow\infty$, the solution $F$ reaches its steady state
$F_*$. Hence, we again set the left-hand side equal zero and solve for
$F_*$.

\begin{align*}
0 = I - \frac{\alpha}{3}F_*^2 \\\Rightarrow \quad F_*^2 = \frac{3I}{\alpha}\\\Rightarrow\quad F_* = \sqrt{\frac{3I}{\alpha}}
\end{align*}

We only consider the positive root since the amount of fish can not be
negative.
